verbs.description: denationalize (third-person singular simple present denationalizes, present participle denationalizing, simple past and past participle denationalized) (American spelling, Oxford British English)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To transfer the control and ownership of an industry from government to private hands; to privatize.
(transitive) To strip of nationhood; to cease to recognise, or allow to exist, as a nation.
examples: Doubtless, in thus denationalizing the Tahitians, as it were, the missionaries were prompted by a sincere desire for good;  […]
